1.  the purpose of sessions is so that people can keep looking at information, even after they close it and re-open it. Or if 
    it contains sensitive information, it can close all sessions so people can get on your computer and see it.

2.  bcrypt helps hash passwords so that they cant be translated 

3.  it adds little bits to the end of passwords to make it more unique

4.  parts of a JSON web token are the header, payload, and signature